## Quarto

Quarto enables you to weave together content and executable code into a
finished document. To learn more about Quarto see <https://quarto.org>.

## Running Code

When you click the **Render** button a document will be generated that
includes both content and the output of embedded code. You can embed
code like this:

```{r tidy=TRUE, tidy.opts=list(width.cutoff=72)}

library(ggplot2)
library(tidyverse)
library(tidyr)
library(DataExplorer)


FishDataSet = read_csv("C:/AppliedDataScienceAndStatistics/Applied-Data-Science-and-Statistics/Term2/CommunicatingDataScience/IndividualReport/HistoricalLandings1950-2010/ICES_1950-2010.csv")

```

You can add options to executable code like this

```{r}
#| echo: false
2 * 2
```

The `echo: false` option disables the printing of code (only output is
displayed).
